# ── Build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PyInstaller intermediates and outputs. The exe is rebuilt from
# Trade_Scanner_FH.spec — never commit the 200 MB binary.
build/
dist/
dist2/
*.exe

# ── Python bytecode / packaging ─────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/

# ── Test / tooling caches ───────────────────────────────────────────
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Virtual environments ────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/

# ── Runtime data (auto-generated by the app; never source) ──────────
# scanner_data/ holds the OHLCV cache, universe snapshot, earnings
# parquets, logs, presets, cookies, and the Firefox profile. The app
# recreates it on launch. Matches it at any depth (package dev copy,
# dist/scanner_data, etc.).
scanner_data/

# ── Secrets / personal data (safety net) ────────────────────────────
# These normally live inside scanner_data/ already, but ignore them
# explicitly so a stray copy can never be committed.
sec_contact.txt
zacks_cookies.txt
*.parquet
*.parquet.bak*

# ── Logs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log

# ── Editor / OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Personal debug artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────
# One-off local debug script (hardcoded personal paths/tickers) — not
# product code, never commit.
_bbcp_dump.py
# Cross-repo review of the author's full personal tool stack — profiles
# private sibling projects; keep local-only.
TRADING_TOOLS_CODE_REVIEW.md
# Live-session page captures written by tests/_zacks_diag.py. Past
# captures embedded the client's real public IP in Imperva iframe
# params (cip=...), so a re-run must never be committable.
_zacks_diag*.html

# ── Misc ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Working screenshot — not a tracked asset (README doesn't reference
# it). Shows real scan output (tickers/filters), so take a fresh
# capture against demo data if a README screenshot is ever wanted.
Screenshot*.png
